Nigerian Wrestler Odunayo Adekuruoye is hoping that the Sports ministry gives the athletes the necessary support as they look forward to the 2021 Tokyo Olympics. She told brila.net that, she believes 2021 will be okay for them and they have already commenced preparations hopefully the sport’s ministry gives them the boost the more to do very well. “I believe 2021 will be okay for us, we have started preparation since 2020 and it shows the ministry and the federation are fully prepared. “Hopefully, the ministry of youths and sports supports us to be on the podium come 2021 Olympics.”  